org.apache.poi.util

Interface POILogger

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CommonsLogger, NullLogger, SLF4JLogger, SystemOutLogger 

    @Internal
public interface POILogger
    A logger interface that strives to make it as easy as possible for developers to write log calls, while simultaneously making those calls as cheap as possible by performing lazy evaluation of the log message. A logger can be selected via system properties, e.g. -Dorg.apache.poi.util.POILogger=org.apache.poi.util.SystemOutLogger The following Logger-implementations are provided:
    • NullLogger
    • CommonsLogger
    • SystemOutLogger
    (一个记录器界面，致力于让开发人员尽可能轻松地编写日志调用，同时通过对日志消息执行懒惰评估来使这些调用尽可能便宜。可以通过系统属性选择记录器，例如-Dorg.apache.poi.util.POILogger=org.apache.poi.util.SystemOutLogger提供了以下记录器实现：NullLogger CommonsLogger SystemOutLogger)

      • _log

        @Internal
void _log(int level,
                    java.lang.Object obj1)
        Log a message - belongs to the SPI, usually not called from user code(记录消息-属于SPI，通常不会从用户代码中调用)
        Parameters:

      • _log

        @Internal
void _log(int level,
                    java.lang.Object obj1,
                    java.lang.Throwable exception)
        Log a message - belongs to the SPI, usually not called from user code(记录消息-属于SPI，通常不会从用户代码中调用)
        Parameters:
        level - One of DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL(级别-调试、信息、警告、错误、致命之一)

      • check

        boolean check(int level)
        Check if a logger is enabled to log at the specified level This allows code to avoid building strings or evaluating functions in the arguments to log. An example: 
         if (logger.check(POILogger.INFO)) {
     logger.log(POILogger.INFO, "Avoid concatenating ", " strings and evaluating ", functions());
 }
        (检查记录器是否已启用以在指定级别进行记录这允许代码避免在参数中构建字符串或评估函数来记录。示例：if（logger.check（POILogger.Info））{ logger.log（POILogger.Info，“避免连接”，“字符串和评估”，functions（））; })
        Parameters:
        level - One of DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL(级别-调试、信息、警告、错误、致命之一)

      • log

        default void log(int level,
                 java.lang.Object... objs)
        Log a message. Lazily appends Object parameters together. If the last parameter is a Throwable it is logged specially.(记录消息。Lazily将对象参数附加在一起。如果最后一个参数是Throwable，则会专门记录它。)
        Parameters:
        level - One of DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR, FATAL(级别-调试、信息、警告、错误、致命之一)
        objs - the objects to place in the message(objs -要放置在消息中的对象)
